      "writtenOn": "2017-04-24T19:28:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It hasn\u0027t come up, and I\u0027m not sure it belongs as a part of this patch, but possibly.\n\nIf the client attempts to decode again, we should rewind, which will delete this one and create a new one. Maybe the client tries to misuse our API, and continue incremental decoding after a failure. That would be a bug on the client\u0027s part, but perhaps it could cause a problem. (I suspect libpng will recognize that it is in a busted state, but I should write a test. They may make the same conclusion I made - caller\u0027s fault.)",
      "parentUuid": "02e149d8_b6ab434f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 188,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 188,
