    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7e384feb_13902c2c",
        "filename": "tests/CodecExactReadTest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-24T18:01:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This particular image works. I think we broke RLE bitmaps with https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/7028/. They\u0027ll now fail for the same reason as WEBP, JPEG, RAW [1], and PNG prior to my fixes. (That said, that was a security bug, so it was backported to earlier versions of Android. So devices from K on will already not work for RLE bitmaps.)\n\nMy reading of the wikipedia page (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BMP_file_format) suggests that the only thing that can come after the pixel data is an ICC profile. It looks like we currently do not read any ICC profile for BMPs, and we just stop reading when we reach the last row, so if there was an ICC profile, this test would fail. But this would not be a regression from N.\n\n(On a related note: GIF currently fails, due to the fact that I only bother to parse the first image, since Android will only ever show the first image. It already failed in N similarly to BMP with ICC - we simply stopped reading once we saw the last line of the image. So no backwards compatibility problem.)\n\n[1] If a RAW image has an embedded JPEG, we\u0027ll fail for a different reason - we only read to the end of the JPEG. Again, this is not a regression.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 53,
        "endChar": 45
      },
